<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Testing Standards | Ursus Armament</title>

<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&family=Barlow:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>
  :root {
    --black: #0a0a08;
    --dark: #111110;
    --surface: #1a1a17;
    --surface2: #222220;
    --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
    --text: #e8e4d9;
    --muted: #8a8678;
    --accent: #c8922a;
    --accent2: #e8a830;
  }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'Barlow', sans-serif;
  }

  nav {
    padding: 1rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: rgba(10,10,8,0.9);
  }

  .nav-logo {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }

  section { padding: 6rem 3rem; }

  .hero {
    padding-top: 10rem;
    padding-bottom: 6rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(10,10,8,0.4), var(--black));
  }

  .section-tag {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed';
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  h1, h2 {
    font-family: 'Bebas Neue';
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  h1 { font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem); }
  h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; }

  p {
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed';
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .lookup {
    background: var(--surface2);
    padding: 3rem;
    margin-top: 4rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .lookup input {
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text);
    width: 250px;
  }

  .btn {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: black;
    padding: 0.8rem 2rem;
    border: none;
    margin-left: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-family: 'Barlow Condensed';
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
</style>
</head>

<body>

<nav>
  <div class="nav-logo">URSUS <span style="color:var(--accent)">ARMAMENT</span></div>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="section-tag">Validation</div>
  <h1>TESTING<br><span style="color:var(--accent)">STANDARDS</span></h1>
  <p>
    Our products are evaluated using environmental testing methodologies derived from MIL-STD-810H,
    focusing on real-world durability, reliability, and sustained performance under stress.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- OVERVIEW -->
<section>
  <div class="section-tag">Framework</div>
  <h2>MIL-STD-810H Approach</h2>
  <p>
    MIL-STD-810H is not a single test, but a framework of environmental methods designed to replicate
    operational stress conditions. We apply these methods selectively based on realistic use cases
    rather than treating the standard as a checklist.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- TEST GRID -->
<section>
  <div class="section-tag">Environmental Methods</div>

  <div class="grid">

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Temperature Extremes</h3>
      <p>High and low temperature exposure to evaluate material stability and function.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Thermal Shock</h3>
      <p>Rapid temperature transitions to test structural integrity and sealing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Water / Rain</h3>
      <p>Simulated precipitation and exposure to evaluate ingress protection.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Dust & Sand</h3>
      <p>Fine particulate intrusion testing for harsh environments.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Vibration</h3>
      <p>Transport and operational vibration across multiple platforms.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Shock / Drop</h3>
      <p>Impact resistance from handling, drops, and sudden force.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- SERIAL LOOKUP -->
<section>
  <div class="section-tag">Verification</div>
  <h2>Serialized Product Records</h2>
  <p>
    Many serialized products include a searchable record containing original specifications and
    testing data. Enter a serial number below to access configuration details and associated
    validation data where applicable.
  </p>

  <div class="lookup">
    <input type="text" placeholder="Enter Serial Number">
    <button class="btn">Search</button>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DISCLAIMER -->
<section>
  <div class="section-tag">Note</div>
  <h2>Compliance & Interpretation</h2>
  <p>
    Use of MIL-STD-810H-derived testing does not imply formal certification unless explicitly stated.
    Test conditions, durations, and procedures are tailored to reflect realistic operational use.
  </p>
</section>

</body>
</html>
